HEADWORD: Blouse
<hw>Blouse</hw> <pr>(blouz; F. bl⟦oomac⟧z)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>blouse</ets>. Of unknown origin.]</ety> <def>A light, loose
over-garment, like a smock frock, worn especially by workingmen in
France; also, a loose coat of any material, as the undress uniform coat
of the United States army.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

